muttlearn (1.2)

  * Many bugfixes
  * Increased performance (8x faster re-indexing), especially for Maildir/MH
  * Add $max_path_length option if your version of mutt can handle more than
    256 characters in $editor
  * Make regular expressions configurable:
    $greeting_regexp and $goodbye_regexp
  * Learn if you prefer to write TOFU or inline when replying
  * Ability to add vim placeholder (e.g. <++>) to greeting, body and goodbye
    message: $template_insert_placeholder
  
 -- Johannes Weißl <jargon@molb.org>  Thu Dec 2 23:33:13 2010 +0100

